Frequently Asked Questions

Still confused about VPNs? Don’t worry we got your back!

Why do I need a VPN?

A VPN encrypts your data and keeps your online activity private, so advertisers, hackers, and other third parties can’t track what you’re doing. A good VPN will also let you access restricted websites, apps, and streaming services, allowing you to browse the internet freely.

Are VPNs legal?

VPNs are perfectly legal in most countries. In some countries, such as China, Russia, Iran, and the UAE, they are regulated or banned. Just keep in mind that while a VPN keeps your identity hidden, illegal activity (such as downloading copyrighted content) still remains illegal.

Is there a 100% free VPN?

There are several free VPNs out there, but we don’t recommend using them. Some of these services are extremely limited in bandwidth and speeds, while others will go so far as to make money by selling your private data to third parties. If you just need a VPN for a short time, you can get premium service for free by signing up for ExpressVPN. All you have to do is request a refund before the 30-day money-back guarantee runs out.

Do I need a VPN for my mobile device?

These days, it’s always a good idea to use a VPN on your smartphone or tablet, especially if you use public Wi-Fi. Mobile devices can be vulnerable, and a good VPN keeps all your online activity - from private chats to banking data - completely secure from hackers and other prying eyes.
